        <h1>FICA Tax Rate 2025: Social Security and Medicare</h1>
        <p class="qa-meta">Updated April 2026 &nbsp;|&nbsp; Based on IRS Publication 15 and SSA announcement &nbsp;|&nbsp; Tax year 2025</p>
        <p>FICA stands for the Federal Insurance Contributions Act. For 2025, employees pay 6.2% for Social Security on wages up to $176,100 and 1.45% for Medicare on all wages. Employers match both. Self-employed individuals pay the combined 15.3% rate.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="quick-answer">
        <div class="qa-label">Quick Answer: 2025 FICA Rates at a Glance</div>
        <h2>Employee share: 7.65% total</h2>
        <div class="rate-grid">
          <div class="rate-item">
            <div class="ri-label">Social Security Rate</div>
            <div class="ri-value">6.2%</div>
            <div class="ri-sub">On wages up to $176,100</div>
          </div>
          <div class="rate-item">
            <div class="ri-label">Medicare Rate</div>
            <div class="ri-value">1.45%</div>
            <div class="ri-sub">On all wages, no limit</div>
          </div>
          <div class="rate-item">
            <div class="ri-label">Social Security Wage Base</div>
            <div class="ri-value">$176,100</div>
            <div class="ri-sub">SS tax stops above this amount</div>
          </div>
          <div class="rate-item">
            <div class="ri-label">Self-Employed Combined Rate</div>
            <div class="ri-value">15.3%</div>
            <div class="ri-sub">Both employee and employer share</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ad-zone">
        <div class="ad-zone-label">Advertisement</div>
        <ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display:block"
          data-ad-client="ca-pub-5193834725888549"
